      "content": "I'll replace your O(n²) brute force with Manacher's algorithm, which runs in O(n) time and guarantees you'll pass the 1-second limit for 100,000 characters.\n```python\ndef longest_palindrome(s):\n    if not s: return \"\"\n    t = '#'.join('^{}$'.format(s))\n    n = len(t)\n    p = [0] * n\n    c, r = 0, 0\n    for i in range(1, n-1):\n        mirror = 2*c - i\n        if i < r:\n            p[i] = min(r-i, p[mirror])\n        while t[i+p[i]] == t[i-p[i]]:\n            p[i] += 1\n        if i+p[i] > r:\n            c, r = i, i+p[i]\n    max_len, center_index = 0, 0\n    for i in range(1, n-1):\n        if p[i] > max_len:\n            max_len, center_index = p[i], i\n    return s[(center_index-max_len)//2",
